249-01||7||HISTORY:  This is a first office visit for this 77-year-old, right-hand-dominant, founder of Bed Bath and Beyond, who comes for evaluation of right greater than left hand and wrist pain.
249-01||8||The patient reports having a longstanding history of greater than four months of worsening pain, paresthesias, and "numbness" on the right worse than left hand.
249-01||9||This is worse at night and does occasionally wake him up from sleep.
249-01||10||Also bothers him during prolonged activity.
249-01||11||He also reports recently over the past few months noting difficulty with the key pinch, grasp, and fine motor function.
249-01||12||Previous evaluation consisted of cervical spine MRI as well as EMG nerve conduction studies demonstrating findings significant for severe compression neuropathy of the median nerve at the level of wrist.
249-01||13||He now comes for evaluation for potential carpal tunnel surgery release.
