249-01||27||Santiago.  At this time, we feel that Larry has indeed a significant, right worse than left, bilateral carpal tunnel syndrome.
249-01||28||Given the amount of weakness and thenar wasting, he has difficulty with abductor pollicis, we have recommended proceeding with both carpal tunnel release as well as  possible FTS of ring finger to thumb tendon transfer.
249-01||29||We discussed with Larry the risks and benefits of this procedure and he is in agreement of the plan.
249-01||30||We will try to schedule him to proceed with surgery at some point in the near future.
